  "result_text": "The script was executed successfully for the **7-bus** project (internally named \"Taller 2\"). It extracted the impedance parameters for all 10 lines in the system, calculating per-km values, total sequence impedances ($Z_1, Z_0$), their angles, and the $K_0$ factor.\n\n### Results Summary\n- **Project**: Taller 2 (7-bus)\n- **Total Lines Processed**: 10\n- **Extracted Parameters**:\n    - **Per-km**: $R_1, X_1, R_0, X_0$ ($\\Omega/km$)\n    - **Totals**: $Z_{1,total}, Z_{0,total}$ ($\\Omega$)\n    - **Angles**: $\\theta_1, \\theta_0$ (degrees)\n    - **Factor**: $K_0 = \\frac{Z_0 - Z_1}{3 \\cdot Z_1}$\n- **Timing**: 0.05 seconds (extraction).\n\n### Impedance Examples\n| Line Name | Length (km) | $Z_{1,total}$ ($\\Omega$) | Angle1 (\u00b0) | $K_0$ Factor |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **L1** | 100.0 | 41.23 | 75.96 | 0.81 |\n| **L2** | 50.0 | 20.62 | 75.96 | 0.81 |\n| **L3** | 120.0 | 49.48 | 75.96 | 0.81 |\n| **L4** | 80.0 | 32.98 | 75.96 | 0.81 |\n| **L5** | 70.0 | 28.86 | 75.96 | 0.81 |\n\nThe full detailed parameters for all lines are available in `results/line_parameters.json`.\n\n### Engineering Note\nIn the `7-bus` model, all lines use standard types where $X_1/R_1 \\approx 4$ and $Z_0 \\approx 3.4 \\cdot Z_1$. This results in a consistent $K_0$ factor of approximately **0.81**. The script correctly identified if parameters were defined in the Line Type (`TypLne`) or manually in the element (`ElmLne`) via the `iopt_typ` attribute.",
